13/02/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The chairmen of the Macedonian and Serbian business chambers, Dusan Petreski and Radoslav Veselinovic, signed an agreement Thursday (12 February) creating the Macedonian-Serbian Business Council.
It would support and promote economic co-operation and facilitate contracts among businesses, as well as boost implementation of the free trade agreement.
Foreign trade between Macedonia and Serbia amounted to $500m last year.
In other developments Thursday, a new Macedonian peacekeeping unit left for Afghanistan to join the International Security Assistance Force there.
The troops will serve with the German contingent.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 13/02/04;
MIA, A1 TV - 12/02/04)
